   <category>
      <pattern>brief information about Mount Picchu</pattern>
      <template>
        Machu Picchu is a 15th-century Inca citadel situated on a mountain ridge 2430 metres (7970 ft) above sea level.It is located in the Cusco Region Urubamba Province Machupicchu District in Peru above the Sacred Valley which is 80 kilometres (50 mi) northwest of Cuzco and through which the Urubamba River flows.
      </template>
   </category>

<category>
      <pattern>architecture about Mount Picchu</pattern>
      <template>
Machu Picchu has about 200 buildings that are considered architectural wonders. These buildings were made of individually shaped pieces of carved gray granite stone that fitted perfectly together. Regular Inca buildings were built with rectangular stones which have 8 corners and 6 sides.
      </template>
   </category>

<category>
      <pattern>history of Mount Picchu</pattern>
      <template>
Tucked away in the rocky countryside northwest of Cuzco Peru Machu Picchu is believed to have been a royal estate or sacred religious site for Inca leaders whose civilization was virtually wiped out by Spanish invaders in the 16th century.
      </template>
   </category>
   
